%% Data Science Pipelines - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / SDK Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS(edge)
    participant UI as ml-pipeline-ui<br/>3000/TCP HTTP
    participant API as ml-pipeline API Server<br/>8888/TCP HTTP<br/>8887/TCP gRPC
    participant K8s as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Argo as Argo Workflows<br/>Controller
    participant PA as Persistence Agent
    participant MW as Metadata Writer
    participant MLMD as metadata-grpc-server<br/>8080/TCP gRPC
    participant Cache as cache-server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant DB as MySQL/PostgreSQL<br/>3306/5432/TCP
    participant S3 as MinIO/S3<br/>9000/TCP HTTP

    Note over User, S3: Flow 1: Pipeline Submission and Execution

    User->>Route: POST /apis/v2beta1/pipelines<br/>HTTPS TLS, Bearer Token
    Route->>UI: Forward (edge TLS termination)
    UI->>API: REST API call<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP, Bearer Token
    API->>DB: Store pipeline metadata<br/>DB protocol, Username/Password
    DB-->>API: Confirmation
    API->>S3: Upload pipeline spec/artifacts<br/>HTTP 9000/TCP, AccessKey/SecretKey
    S3-->>API: Upload confirmation

    User->>API: POST /apis/v2beta1/runs<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP, Bearer Token
    API->>DB: Store run record
    API->>K8s: Create Workflow CR<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP, SA Token
    K8s-->>API: Workflow created
    Argo->>K8s: Watch & execute Workflow<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP, SA Token

    Note over User, S3: Flow 2: Pipeline Execution Monitoring

    PA->>K8s: Watch Workflows<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP, SA Token (3600s expiry)
    K8s-->>PA: Workflow status updates
    PA->>API: Report execution status<br/>HTTP 8888/TCP, SA Token

    MW->>K8s: Watch Workflows<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP, SA Token
    K8s-->>MW: Workflow completion events
    MW->>MLMD: Write execution metadata<br/>gRPC 8080/TCP, plaintext

    Note over User, S3: Flow 3: Pipeline Step Caching

    K8s->>Cache: Admission webhook call<br/>HTTPS 443->8443/TCP, TLS cert
    Cache->>DB: Check cache entries<br/>DB protocol, Username/Password
    DB-->>Cache: Cache hit/miss
    Cache-->>K8s: Mutated pod spec (skip if cached)

    Note over User, S3: Flow 4: Scheduled Workflow Execution

    Note right of API: ScheduledWorkflow Controller<br/>watches ScheduledWorkflow CRs
    API->>K8s: Watch ScheduledWorkflow CRs<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP, SA Token (3600s expiry)
    K8s-->>API: Schedule trigger
    API->>K8s: Create Workflow CR<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP, SA Token
